just_use board_classifier.py

# label: EARLY
# role: tag every card and stack on a board with strategic adjectives

Produces the typed-board view a planner reads: per-card and
per-stack adjective sets (`loose`, `peelable`, etc., per
`random008.md`'s vocabulary). The "what roles can each
thing play?" layer — derived once instead of recomputed
per-verb.

Currently used by `dsl_planner.py`. The newer `bfs_solver.py`
operates on the 4-bucket model directly and does not consume
this typed view.

